                    <h2 style="text-shadow: 2px 2px 2px #7b9de2; font-family: cursive; color: gray;"><em>Protecting the home, food & safety of threatened species</em></h2>
                    <p>
                        Australia has already lost more mammal species in the last 200 years than every other country in the world combined.
                        Koalas are declining at a rate of 21% per decade and could be gone from the wild in NSW by 2050, along with many other
                        uniquely Australian species who are losing their forest homes.

                        Global wildlife populations have declined by 60% since 1970 . Tigers are endangered and on the brink of extinction –
                        with as few as 3,900 left in the wild. In Borneo, orangutans are losing their homes and their lives - they’re now listed
                        as critically endangered. But you can help.
                    </p>
